What Is Mortadella,Â Exactly?


â€œMortadellaâ€ is a catchall term to describe a cold cut made from pork scraps and pieces of pork fat, which gets added to the mixture in cubes and gives mortadella its telltale white polka dots when sliced. If you want to be more specific, â€œtrueâ€ mortadella would be Mortadella Bologna, a protected geographical indication (PGI) product made in select Italian regions.


